Android 11大约在三个月前问世，这意味着三星终于有时间共同行动起来，开始发售该操作系统。三星在其公司博客上宣布，只要您位于韩国，美国和欧洲大多数市场，Galaxy S20，S20 +和S20 Ultra都将立即开始使用Android 11。 ;
 最新发布的Android版本推迟了三个月，与三星去年在Android 10上所做的一样，当时这是该公司创纪录的速度。当然，三星的产品线不只是S20，而且该公司的官方时间表中还有Note20，Z Fold 2和Z Flip等到1月。三星最畅销的设备全部来自中端的GalaxyA。线，并且这些更新会在3月到6月的任何时间进行更新，因此会在Android 11发布后的6到9个月的任何时间更新。
     在绝对庞大的Android 10版本发布以及一年困扰COVID问题的一年之后，Google并未在Android 11中进行大量更改。通知面板具有一个新的持久性媒体播放器，一个历史记录部分，并支持浮动气泡通知。麦克风，摄像头和位置获得了新的一次性许可批准，新的表情符号，在模块化方面的工作更多，自动填充更轻松。当然，在三星手机上，所有这些都通过自定义UI（三星的一个UI）铺平了道路，并且皮肤也随着Android一起更新。 Android Police具有出色的Beta版动手功能，表明大多数Android 11功能均完好无损，并且具有新的音量滑块UI和其他一些轻巧的功能。与往常一样，首次展示可能需要数周时间才能影响您的设备，因此即使您拥有Galaxy S20，也不要指望立即进行更新。现在它正在向一小部分人推广，而在三星等待听到任何问题时，它会慢慢增加。如果您还没有更新通知，请继续等待。

note_en:
Android 11 came out  about three months ago, and that means it&#39;s finally time for Samsung to get its act together and start shipping the OS out. Samsung announced on  its company blog that the Galaxy S20, S20+, and S20 Ultra would all start getting Android 11 right now, provided you&#39;re in &#34;Korea, the US, and most markets in Europe.&#34;
 A three-month delay on the latest Android release is on par with what Samsung  did last year for Android 10, which, at the time, was a record pace for the company. Of course, Samsung&#39;s lineup is more than just the S20, and the company&#39;s  official timeline has the  Note20,  Z Fold 2, and  Z Flip waiting until January. Samsung&#39;s  best-selling devices are all from the midrange &#34;Galaxy A&#34; line, and those are getting updated anywhere from March to June, so anywhere from six to nine months after Android 11&#39;s release.
     After the absolutely massive  Android 10 release and a year plagued with COVID issues, Google didn&#39;t pack a huge amount of changes into Android 11. The notification panel has a new persistent media player, a history section, and support for floating bubble notifications. There are new one-time permission approvals for the microphone, camera, and location, new emojis, more work toward modularity, and easier autofill. Of course, on a Samsung phone, this is all getting paved over with a custom UI—Samsung&#39;s &#34;One UI&#34;—and that skin is getting updated along with Android.  Android Police has a great hands-on of the beta, showing that most of the Android 11 features are intact, along with things like a new volume slider UI and a few other light touches. As always, rollouts can take weeks to hit your device, so even if you have a Galaxy S20, don&#39;t expect the update right away. It&#39;s rolling out now to a small population, which will slowly increase while Samsung waits to hear about any problems. If you don&#39;t have the update notification yet, keep waiting.
